CCLV· Presentation of Alexander Bissat minister at the kirk of Brechin to the

parsonage and vicarage of Kylmoir, with the emoluments‚ manse, and glebe thereof, by John Livingstoun of Donypace patron thereos, proceeding on the narrative that the persons dwelling formerly within the parish of Kylmoir were then within the parish of Brechin, and there received the word and sa- craments‚ and that the said vicarage and parsonage was vacant by the decease of Mr. Andrew Leich‚ last parson and vicar thereof. Signed before these witnesses, John Straitoun fiar of Lowrenstoun‚ David Barclay of Matheris, Patrik Levingstoun of Balrowny‚ Peter Blair in Liehtownhssl, and John Noray notary in Brechin, 26 October, 1611.
